threat_severity.level_description: Severity MEDIUM because it was considered trojan.

attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, ARM, EABI4 version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This is an ARM-based malware that compromises the system's network security by aggressively manipulating firewall rules. It flushes all existing `iptables` rules and adds new ones to allow traffic, likely for C2 communication. The malware also performs anti-forensics by attempting to clear log files and shell history. Key malicious behaviors include executing `iptables -F`, `iptables -X` on filter, nat, and mangle tables, removing all files from `/tmp` (`rm -rf /tmp/*`), and clearing `/var/log/wtmp` and `.bash_history`.
